  "prompt": "How do I find my lost mobile using IMEI?",
  "response": "To find your lost mobile using its IMEI number, follow these steps:\n\n1. Contact Your Mobile Carrier\n- Call your mobile service provider\n- Provide them with the IMEI number\n- Request they track or block the device\n- They may help locate the phone or disable its network access\n\n2. File a Police Report\n- Report the lost/stolen phone to local law enforcement\n- Provide the IMEI number\n- This creates an official record and can help in recovery\n\n3. Use Find My Device Services\n- For Android: Use Google's \"Find My Device\" website\n- For iPhone: Use \"Find My iPhone\" through iCloud\n- These services can help locate, lock, or erase your device\n\n4. Online IMEI Tracking Services\n- Some websites claim to track phones via IMEI\n- Be cautious of potential scams\n- Verify the legitimacy of such services\n\n5. Prevention Tips\n- Note down your IMEI number beforehand\n- Keep it in a safe place\n- You can find it by dialing *#06# or checking phone settings\n\n6. If Unable to Recover\n- Consider remotely wiping your device\n- Change passwords for important accounts\n- Contact your carrier to suspend service\n\nRemember, success depends on various factors like the phone being turned on and connected to a network.",
